quran[3]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,10,"There is a disease in their hearts and Allah has intensified this disease.{1} A painful chastisement awaits them for their lying.",footnotes:1:' Disease' here refers to the disease of hypocrisy. The statement that 'Allah has intensified this disease' means that He does not punish the hypocrites immediately but allows them to indulge in their hypocrisy and exult in the success of their ruses. This feeling of success intensifies their hypocrisy.
  2,11,"Whenever they are told: “Do not spread mischief on earth,” they say: “Why! We indeed are the ones who set things right.”"
  2,12,"They are the mischief makers, but they do not realize it."